Note:          Specially designed or prepared equipment for the fabrication of "nuclear reactor" fuel elements
          includes equipment which:
<br>&emsp;                                   1.     Normally comes into direct contact with or directly processes or controls the production flow of
                                           nuclear materials;
<br>&emsp;                                   2.     Seals the nuclear materials within the cladding;
<br>&emsp;                                   3.     Checks the integrity of the cladding or the seal;
<br>&emsp;                                   4.     Checks the finish treatment of the sealed fuel; or
<br>&emsp;                                   5.     Is used for assembling reactor elements.

0C001 does not control the following:<br>                                   a.    Four grammes or less of "natural uranium" or "depleted uranium" when contained in a sensing
                                           component in instruments;
<br>                                   b.    "Depleted uranium" specially fabricated for the following civil non-nuclear applications:
<br>&emsp;                                          1.     Shielding;
<br>&emsp;                                          2.     Packaging;
<br>&emsp;                                          3.     Ballasts having a mass not greater than 100 kg;
<br>&emsp;                                          4.     Counter-weights having a mass not greater than 100 kg;
<br>                                   c.    Alloys containing less than 5% thorium;
<br>                                   d.    Ceramic products containing thorium, which have been manufactured for non-nuclear use.

